    "comment": "Rationale: Immunogold EM of rat spinal cord showed substance P (gene TAC1) and serotonin particles at large dense core vesicles in the same presynape. The presented EM image does not show a postsynaptic structure, authors comment on this and mention this was observed in multiple images (data not shown).\n\nSimilarly, Bolam et al. (PMID:2454839) reported presynaptic substance P was observed at symmetric synapses in rat neostriatum.. Experimental description: \"Adult male rats were fixed by perfusion in 300 ml of glutaraldehyde in 0.1 M cacodylate buffer (pH 7.6); raphe nuclei of the medulla oblongata and ventral horn of the spinal cord were carefully dissected and post-fixed by immersion for 1 h in 0.5% OS04 diluted in the same cacodylate buffer.\"",
